<SECOND>PM-People-Buffett,0236</SECOND>
<HEAD>Investor Warren Buffett Has Bit Part On ABC Soap</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> <PERSON> Buffett </PERSON>, a corporate takeover specialist whose company holds a major stake in <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> television, says he does n't expect an award for his appearance as a bartender in an episode of an ABC-TV soap opera. <PERSON> Buffett </PERSON> is joined in the scene for `` Loving'', scheduled to air today, by the show's creator, <PERSON> Agnes </PERSON> <PERSON> Nixon </PERSON>, and <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON>, chairman of apital Cities-ABC. `` They were wise. They did n't trust us with any dialogue,'' <PERSON> Buffett </PERSON> said Thursday. He said he has seen a tape of the show and was n't too impressed with his performance. `` For a town that produced <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> Fonda </PERSON>, <PERSON> Marlon </PERSON> <PERSON> Brando </PERSON> and <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> <PERSON> Astaire </PERSON>, I'm a sad commentary, I'll tell you,'' he said. <PERSON> Buffett </PERSON>'s Omaha-based company, <ORGANIZATION> Berkshire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hathaway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, is the largest shareholder of <ORGANIZATION> Capital </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cities-ABC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which owns the television network. The scene is set in a restaurant where <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON> plays a waiter and Miss <PERSON> Nixon </PERSON> portrays a customer. During the scene, <PERSON> Buffett </PERSON>'s bartender character and waiter <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON> are summoned by a headwaiter to eject an unruly young woman from the bar, <PERSON> Buffett </PERSON> said. None of the three cameo performers spoke in the scene, he said. <PERSON> Buffett </PERSON> said he was invited to appear on `` Loving'' by <PERSON> Miss </PERSON> <PERSON> Nixon </PERSON>, whom he met at a dinner party at the Winter Olympics in <LOCATION> Calgary </LOCATION>.
