 Here is the 201-181 roll call Thursday by which the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> approved a $ 1.1 trillion fiscal 1989 federal budget. A `` yes'' vote is a vote for the budget. Voting yes were 175 Democrats and 26 Republicans. Voting no were 47 Democrats and 134 Republicans. Y is a yes vote. N is a no vote. X denotes those not voting. Present denotes those who voted they were `` present'' at the time of the vote but id not vote `` yes'' or `` no'' on the issue. There are three vacancies in the 435-member House.
