<SECOND>BC-House Contra Aid Roll Call, 3 Takes,</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Contra Aid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here is the 214-190 roll call by which the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> on Thursday defeated an amendment to lift a ban on use of <ORGANIZATION> CIA </ORGANIZATION> contingency funds to aid <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>'s Contra rebels. A `` yes'' vote is a vote to lift the ban. Voting yes were 41 Democrats and 149 Republicans. Voting no were 197 Democrats and 17 Republicans. Y is a yes vote. N is a no vote. X denotes those not voting. Present denotes those who voted they were `` present'' at the time of the vote but did not vote `` yes'' or `` no'' on the issue. There are three vacancies in the 435-member House.
</TEXT>
