 she said. `` It is very easy to take a few steps with Jewish people. everybody knows the support we have, so they -LRB- the Soviets -RRB- made some steps and everybody applauded.' Mrs. <PERSON> Rosnovsky </PERSON> has been battling for her family every since she left them behind in 1974. She said her father was allowed to leave in 1976 following the intervention of <PERSON> Golda </PERSON> <PERSON> Meir </PERSON>, then retired as <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> prime minister, with contacts in the <ORGANIZATION> Socialist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Internationale </ORGANIZATION>. Her mother spent more than three years in a psychiatric prison, but was released a few years ago and came to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>.
