Keffler, police said. <LOCATION> Seminole </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> sheriff's Sgt. <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Human </PERSON> and Deputy <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Yolton </PERSON> said <PERSON> Klaver </PERSON> moved into an office also used by attorney <PERSON> Angela </PERSON> <PERSON> Blakeley </PERSON> after telling her he was being placed on a list of lawyers available for court-appointed work. <PERSON> Klaver </PERSON> began taking cases and accepting fees. `` He appeared legitimate,'' said Ms. <PERSON> Blakeley </PERSON>. `` All his references checked out.'' Officials discovered the ruse after a man charged with writing bad checks complained that his lawyer had abandoned him after collecting a $ 200 retainer. Investigators have asked the state attorney's office to file charges of forgery, obtaining property by false impersonation and theft against <PERSON> Klaver </PERSON>. A spokesman for the <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bar </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Butterfield </PERSON>, said the bar may have to tighten controls on its ID cards, possibly adding photographs. Ms. <PERSON> Blakeley </PERSON> said that when <PERSON> Klaver </PERSON> disappeared, he took more than $ 10,000 in law books and computer equipment, including all her business records, and collected about $ 10,000 from her own clients. He fled in a car he bought under the name and credit rating of <PERSON> Keffler </PERSON>, authorities said.
