 share for `` Cosby'' indicates fewer sets in use at the earlier time period. The highest-rated miniseries was <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Something Is Out There,'' with a 19.2 and 30 share. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Bourne Identity'' was second with 18.5 and 30. Though miniseries are shorter and fewer, their ratings show them to be `` still a viable programming source,'' said <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> analyst <PERSON> Gerald </PERSON> <PERSON> Jaffe </PERSON>. `` You just have to be careful which ones you make and when you schedule them.''
