see a very clear distinction between the Soviet attitude to the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> and to <LOCATION> Syria </LOCATION>, for example,'' he said. `` <LOCATION> Syria </LOCATION> is a very important asset, the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> less so. They will not sell the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> down the river easily, but they feel what they have to do to protect the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> is less.'' The Soviet position paper was prepared by <PERSON> Alexander </PERSON> <PERSON> Zotov </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>'s deputy director for the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>, the official said, adding that <PERSON> Peres </PERSON> met with a <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> delegation first in <LOCATION> Madrid </LOCATION>, during a a <ORGANIZATION> Socialist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> conference, and then in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Geneva </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Chaim </PERSON> <PERSON> Billat </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Talmudic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Publications </ORGANIZATION>, directed by Rabbi <PERSON> Adin </PERSON> <PERSON> Steinsaltz </PERSON>, announced the research project Thursday. He also said the <PERSON> Steinsaltz </PERSON> would be allowed to open an institute in the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> to train Jewish scholars. `` We consider this as a major breakthrough, and what is important is that it was the Soviet initiative,'' <PERSON> Billat </PERSON> said. The <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> severed diplomatic ties with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> after the 1967 <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LO