<HEAD>Scriptwriters OK Independent Contracts With 70 TV, Movie Producers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By GEORGE GARTIES</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Striking TV and movie scriptwriters will resume work for more than 70 producers, including makers of the top-rated `` The Cosby Show,'' under independent contracts approved by the writers' union Friday. The independent contracts were approved by 86 percent of the 2,016 members of the <ORGANIZATION> Writers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guild </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> who voted Thursday night in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, said union spokeswoman <PERSON> Cheryl </PERSON> <PERSON> Rhoden </PERSON>. The producers' bargaining group, the <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Picture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Television </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Producers </ORGANIZATION>, dismissed the defections of the mostly small production companies as an insignificant episode in the 12-week strike, which has forced delays in the start of the fall television season. By Friday noon, a union list of producers who had signed included <ORGANIZATION> Carsey-Werner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, which makes `` Cosby,'' and the makers of `` The Tonight Show Starring <PERSON> Johnny </PERSON> <PERSON> Carson </PERSON>,'' `` Highway to Heaven'' and `` It's <PERSON> Garry </PERSON> <PERSON> Shandling </PERSON>'s Show.'' Alliance spokesman <PERSON> Herb </PERSON> <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON> estimated the independent contracts, which accede to writers' key pay demands, cover just 1 percent of the union's 3,000 working members, and none of the big production companies that form the backbone of the industry group. `` It had virtually no impact on prime-time network -LRB- programs -RRB-,'' <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON> said of the vote. `` Not one alliance member is in this group,'' <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON> said of the producers who had signed on. `` They voted to put 72 writers to work ... we're concerned with getting 3,000 writers back to work.'' Many of those who signed were one-person writer-producer companies, and some listed make TV shows that have been canceled, including the <ORGANIZATION> Smothers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brothers </ORGANIZATION>' comedy show and `` Days and Nights of <PERSON> Molly </PERSON> <PERSON> Dodd </PERSON>,'' <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON> said. But Ms. <PERSON> Rhoden </PERSON> termed the defections a symbolic victory as well as a break in management ranks. `` We're very, very pleased,'' Ms. <PERSON> Rhoden </PERSON> said. `` The significant thing is that upwards of 70 companies ... feel they can do profitable business under a contract that also respects the needs of writers.'' The three-year contract accepts the writers key demand: Retention of the present formula for the payments, known as residuals, which writers get for reruns of one-hour television shows. Citing the increasing difficulty in selling such shows for rerun, the producers are seeking to link the amount of the residual payments to a show's success in rerun, or syndication as it is known in the industry. The contract also boosts residual payments for use of the writers' work overseas and tightens requirements that writers be consulted about script changes made during filming. The union contract also boosts minimum pay scales for writers. The writers walked out March 7, and until this week, only one bargaining session was held. Talks Wednesday at the producers' headquarters in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>' <LOCATION> Sherman </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Oaks </LOCATION> district failed to make progress The negotiators agreed to resume formal talks Tuesday under the guidance of a federal mediator, and small groups were scheduled to hold preliminary discussions Saturday.
