ca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> First </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Companies </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Omaha </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Neb. </LOCATION>, and share equally in tax benefits arising from the transaction. Eureka, with $ 1.74 billion in assets as of March 31, was founded in 1937. It's been in trouble since the early 1980s, when interest rates soared, leaving many S & amp; Ls holding low-rate mortgages. The bank board, in a release, also attributed the insolvency to `` unsafe and unsound loan underwriting practices.'' <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> board Chairman, <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Danny </PERSON> <PERSON> Wall </PERSON>, the top federal regulator of <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Ls, said the rescue was `` especially significant'' because of the amount of private investment in the deal, which is a record for an S & amp; L rescue. `` This transaction is further evidence ... that the thrift industry is a good place to invest for the future,'' <PERSON> Wall </PERSON> said in a statement. The Eureka deal is the 34th bailout or shutdown of a failed S & amp; L. Twenty-three of the 34 were acquired by investors or merged with existing institutions with <ORGANIZATION> FSLIC </ORGANIZATION> assistance.
