going to give up claim to power, possible violence, other.</NOTE>
<HEAD>With AM-Panama</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto PAN1</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOSEPH B. FRAZIER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Deposed President <PERSON> Eric </PERSON> <PERSON> Arturo </PERSON> <PERSON> Delvalle </PERSON> said from hiding on Friday that he warned the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> in vain against go-it-alone tactics in talks with Gen. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>. He also predicted violence if <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> does n't leave. <PERSON> Delvalle </PERSON> said other Latin American democracies offered to help and that they and the Panamanian opposition should have had a role. He has been in hiding since his ouster in late February. He met with a few correspondents Friday morning at a location the journalists agreed not to disclose. On Wednesday, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials announced that their talks with <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> to resolve the struggle over <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>'s leadership had fallen apart. Secretary of State <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> blamed the collapse on <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>. <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, the de facto leader of <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> as head of the nation's 15,000-member military and police forces, is under indictment in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> as a drug trafficker `` I have always thought that -LRB- the talks -RRB- were a ploy to delay matters, to give -LRB- <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> -RRB- time to strengthen his inner circle within the Panamanian Defense Forces and at the end, yes, to ridicule President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Delvalle </PERSON> said. `` I do n't think -LRB- <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> -RRB- was sincere, and I told the -LRB- <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> -RRB- administration that what happened would happen. That was n't very difficult. I told them about three weeks ago,'' he said. `` I am disappointed at the fact that they did not use to