the military status of some Greek islands and the divided <LOCATION> Mediterranean </LOCATION> island of <LOCATION> Cyprus </LOCATION>. In March 1987, they came to the brink of war over seabed oil drilling rights. But <PERSON> Papoulias </PERSON> said the ministers delayed discussion of `` large issues'' such as the presence of Turkish troops on <LOCATION> Cyprus </LOCATION> for <PERSON> Ozal </PERSON>'s visit. The officials abolished abolished visa rules for diplomats in each other's capitals and agreed to continue talks on cooperation against narcotics, smuggling and terrorism.
