<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> European </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Economic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Community </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> criticized the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> Friday for cuts in required wheat set-aside acreage, which will take less land out of production this year than last. `` There seems to be a fairly flagrant contradiction between what the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> claims to do and what it is doing,'' said a <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> official, who asked not to be named. Both the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> are using programs to take land out of production as a way to cut agricultural overproduction. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> had adjusted its support levels for wheat farmers by announcing earlier this week that they would have to cut planted acreage by only 10 percent this year in order to qualify for government subsidies. Last year they had been forced to cut acreage by 27.5 percent. Each year at this time the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> administration announces price supports and acreage requirements for subsidies under various programs. The <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> spokesman said it remained determined to continue with its own set-aside programs, calling it unfortunate that <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> was taking this action so soon before the mid-term review of the <LOCATION> Uruguay </LOCATION> round of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade talks to be held at the end of this year. The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> administration has called for an end to all agricultural subsidies in both the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and the 12-nation <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> by the year 2000. The trade bloc has criticized the goal as unrealistic.
