ch we offer and the other exchanges offer.'' `` If you take stock index futures and move them to the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> where they would become simply one of many things the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> oversees, we do n't feel there's the expertise there to oversee them correctly,'' <PERSON> Yemma </PERSON> said. He also said recent reports examining the causes of the stock crash have criticized the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION>'s regulatory work, but have not faulted the futures commission's job. `` There have been efforts by certain members of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and certain members of the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> to move regulation of stock index futures to the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> for years,'' <PERSON> Yemma </PERSON> said. `` It's basically politics and turf.''
