<HEAD>Martinez Asks Government to Delay Drilling Off Keys</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Gov. <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Martinez </PERSON> asked the federal government Friday to delay oil and gas drilling off <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>'s southwest coast and the <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Keys </LOCATION> <PERSON> Martinez </PERSON> wrote a letter to <ORGANIZATION> Interior </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Hodel </PERSON> asking for more time to study potential environmental damage from any oil spills before any exploratory drilling is allowed. The governor also said he would reject requests for permits to drill in areas leased by the <ORGANIZATION> Interior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> in 1984 and 1985 if such activities threaten the Keys or <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>. `` It is critical that we have a detailed understanding of the currents in the eastern Gulf -LRB- of <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> -RRB- and <LOCATION> Straits </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> to ensure the protection of the <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Keys </LOCATION>, home of the nation's only living coral reef and countless other irreplaceable resources,'' <PERSON> Martinez </PERSON> wrote The only permit request the governor has received so far is from <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, which wants to drill as many as 23 test wells north of the Dry Tortugas, which are west of <LOCATION> Key </LOCATION> <LOCATION> West </LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> governor also wrote a separate letter to <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>'s congressional delegation, vowing to continue discussing the state's opposition to offshore drilling with officials in the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration. He assured them he would take whatever actions are necessary to protect the Keys and other sensitive coast